## 🛠️ Communication Toolbox

There are **five approved communication methods**.

Choosing the right one is critical.

---

| Tool | Description | Best Use Case |
|------|------------|--------------|
| 🎯 **Direct Reference** | Hard link (`GetComponent`, `[SerializeField]`) | Intra-system links |
| 🤝 **Interface** | Contract-based interaction | Polymorphism, Raycasts |
| 🔍 **Service Locator** | Global interface registry | Core systems access |
| 📡 **Event** | Decoupled broadcast | Fire-and-forget |
| 🧮 **Static Methods** | Pure functions | Math & data transforms |

---

> [!NOTE]
> **Event Timing**
>
> Events can be:
> - Immediate  
> - End-of-frame queued  
>
> Choose based on urgency.

---

### 🔗 Intra-System Communication

Inside the **same system**, prefer:

- ✅ **Direct References** (`GetComponent`, cached in `Awake`)  
- ✅ **Service Locator** (to keep prefabs clean)

---

> [!WARNING]
> This is not absolute.
>
> If using the **Inspector** improves workflow and clarity, prefer it.  
> Avoid dogma — optimize for **clarity + usability**.

---

## 🧭 Golden Rules of System Communication

When a system needs to communicate, ask these:

---

### ❓ Q1: Do I need a return value *right now*?

- 🟢 **YES (Lower Layer)** → Use **Service Locator**  
  *Example: Reading save data*

- 🟡 **YES (Same Layer)** → Use **Interface** or **Blackboard**  
  *Avoid Service Locator coupling between gameplay systems*

- 🔵 **YES (Math/Data)** → Use **Static Function**  
  *Pure computation only*

- 🔴 **NO** → Use **Events**

---

### ❓ Q2: Am I targeting a physical world object?

- 🟢 **YES** → Use **Direct Reference** or **Interface**

**Typical flow:**
```csharp
if (hit.collider.TryGetComponent<IInteractable>(out var interactable))
{
    interactable.Interact();
}
```

> Physics acts as a **spatial decoupler**  
> → You don’t need to know the concrete type

---

### ❓ Q3: Am I communicating with a lower layer?

- 🔴 **No return value** → **Event**
  - Fire-and-forget
  - Safe if receiver fails

- 🟢 **Needs return value** → **Service Locator**

---

## 📋 Communication Cheat Sheet

Use this when reviewing PRs or designing systems:

---

| Scenario | Target | Tool | Example |
|----------|--------|------|--------|
| Instant logic | Stateless | 🧮 Static | `CombatMath.CalculateCrit(ref stats)` |
| Spatial interaction | World entity | 🎯 Raycast + Interface | `TryGetComponent<IInteractable>()` |
| Immediate data | Core layer | 🔍 Service Locator | `Services.Data.ReadSlot(1)` |
| Shared state | Same layer | 🤝 Blackboard | `LevelBlackboard.IsRaining` |
| Fire & forget | Any | 📡 Event | `EventBus.Fire(new AudioEvent("jump"))` |

